        <DIV1>
            <HEADING>Suicide</HEADING>
            <DEATH>
                <DIV2>
                    <CHRONSTRUCT RELEVANCE="SELECTIVE" CHRONCOLUMN="BRITISHWOMENWRITERS" RESP="SIB"> <DATE>10 September 1889</DATE> <CHRONPROSE>AL committed <CAUSE>suicide</CAUSE> at her parents&apos; home at <PLACE><ADDRESS><ADDRLINE>7 Endsleigh Gardens</ADDRLINE></ADDRESS>, <SETTLEMENT CURRENT="London">Bloomsbury</SETTLEMENT><REGION REG="Middlesex"></REGION><GEOG REG="England"></GEOG></PLACE>, by burning charcoal in a small enclosed room, till she was <CAUSE>asphyxiated by carbon monoxide</CAUSE>.</CHRONPROSE> <BIBCITS><BIBCIT PLACEHOLDER="Beckman 201" DBREF="8347">201</BIBCIT></BIBCITS> </CHRONSTRUCT>
                    <SHORTPROSE>
                        <P>The following year the novelist <NAME>Grant Allen</NAME>, an opponent of higher education for women, attributed her suicide directly to her time at university. Beckman considers many possible reasons&mdash;a broken love-affair, her lesbianism, her deafness, the growing antisemitism of English society, the hostile reception of <TITLE TITLETYPE="MONOGRAPHIC">Reuben Sachs</TITLE>, possible fears of inherited insanity, or simple body chemistry&mdash;but comes to no definite conclusion.<BIBCITS><BIBCIT PLACEHOLDER="Beckman 3, 7, 203-10, 318" DBREF="8347">3, 7, 203-210, 318</BIBCIT></BIBCITS><SCHOLARNOTE> <P>As to her sensitivity to adverse criticism, in 1884 she had written of herself and <NAME>Ernest Radford</NAME>, <QUOTE DIRECT="Y">It&apos;s a good thing we are not of <NAME STANDARD="Keats, John">Keats</NAME>-like sensibility, otherwise we shd. long ago have been <QUOTE DIRECT="N">snuffed out</QUOTE> by the various <QUOTE DIRECT="N">articles</QUOTE> of kind critics.</QUOTE><BIBCITS><BIBCIT PLACEHOLDER="Beckman 248" DBREF="8347" QTDIN="QTDINYES">248</BIBCIT></BIBCITS></P> </SCHOLARNOTE></P>
                        <P>On 13 September AL became the first Jewish woman to be cremated in <PLACE><GEOG>England</GEOG></PLACE>. Her ashes are buried at <PLACE><PLACENAME>Balls Pond Cemetery</PLACENAME> in <SETTLEMENT>London</SETTLEMENT><REGION REG="Middlesex"></REGION><GEOG REG="England"></GEOG></PLACE>.<BIBCITS><BIBCIT PLACEHOLDER="DLB 156: 214" DBREF="9286">214</BIBCIT></BIBCITS></P>
                    </SHORTPROSE>
                </DIV2>
